{"_id":"Squashwithtomatoesandbacon","preptime":"15","servings":"4","keywords":["cook method.hob, oven, grill@hob","diet@peanut-free","occasion@halloween","diet@wheat-free","diet@corn-free","diet@citrus-free","diet@yeast-free","diet@shellfish-free","main ingredient@vegetables","scalability@good for numbers","main ingredient@meat","meal type@main","convenience@add bread for complete meal","diet@egg-free","diet@gluten-free","special collections@weekday meal"],"subtitle":"This dish makes a quick and tasty supper. Best simply served with hot, crusty bread.","totaltime":"46","cooktime":"31","ingredients":[{"ingredient":"dried marjoram","measure":"[sup]1[/sup]/[sub]2[/sub] tsp"},{"ingredient":"dried thyme","measure":"[sup]1[/sup]/[sub]2[/sub] tsp"},{"ingredient":"onion","measure":"1"},{"ingredient":"sunflower oil","measure":"6 tsp"},{"ingredient":"cheddar cheese","measure":"50 g"},{"ingredient":"canned chopped tomatoes","measure":"400 g"},{"ingredient":"back bacon","measure":"4 rashers"},{"ingredient":"garlic","measure":"2 cloves"},{"ingredient":"fresh thyme","measure":"1 tsp"},{"ingredient":"fresh marjoram","measure":"1 tsp"},{"ingredient":"fresh chives","measure":"3 tsp"},{"ingredient":"squash","measure":"675 g"},{"ingredient":"parmesan cheese","measure":"3 tsp"},{"ingredient":"tomato puree","measure":"6 tsp"}],"method":[{"step":"1","text":"In a large saucepan, heat the oil over a moderate heat. Add onions, garlic and bacon and cook for 5 min or until onion is softened. "},{"step":"2","text":"Stir in tomatoes, tomato puree, thyme, marjoram and squash. Bring to the boil then reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20-30 min or until the squash is tender. "},{"step":"3","text":"Sprinkle over the chives and Cheddar. Spoon into a warmed serving dish. Sprinkle over the Parmesan cheese to serve."}],"title":"Squash with tomatoes and bacon"}